Mandelbrot
source|
url|
aliases|
tags|
activeTime|
totalTime|
yield|4 dozen cookies
description|piscotie like. Can be frozen for up to 3 months.

# ingredients
1|cup|granulated sugar
3/4|cup|salad oil or shortening (canola oil, etc.)
3||eggs
1/4|tsp|salt
3|cup|unsifted all purpose flour
1|tsp|anise seed
1|cup|finely chopped walnuts

# instructions
Preheat 350 degrees.
In large bowl, with eletric mixer at medium speed, beat sugar, oil and eggs till well blended.
Add flour, salt, and anise seed. Cotinue beating till well mixed.
Stir in walnuts by hand.
Divide dough in half.
On cookie sheet, with floured hands, shape each half into 12 by 3 inch loafs, about 3 iches apart, or on separate sheets.
Bake 20-25 minutes or until lightly brown.
Remove from oven and immediatley cut each loaf crosswise into 1/2 inch diagonal slices. turn each slice on side and return to oven to back for 15-20 minutes, till lightly brown. Turn occasionally during baking.
